LAFIA- The Nasarawa State House of Assembly on Monday received the report of the House Joint Committee on Housing and Environment / Health on a Bill for a Law to Establish the Nasarawa State Waste Management and Sanitation Authority (NASWAMSA) and for other Connected matters. Rt. Hon. Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, the speaker of the House who received the report slated 22nd March, 2021 for deliberation of the bill after Hon Luka Iliya Zhekaba, the Chairman of the Joint Committee presented its report during the House proceedings in the flour of the House. The speaker said that the bill if passed into law would ensure environmental cleanliness and would control waste in the state. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! “I will slate 22nd March, 2021 for deliberation of the report of the House Joint Committee on Housing and Environment / Health on a Bill for a Law to Establish the Nasarawa State Waste Management and Sanitation Authority ( NASWAMSA) and for other Connected matters,” he said. The speaker applauded the effort of the committee for a job well done . Do Not Abandon Projects Started By Your Predecessors, Okowa Warns Newly Elected LG Chairmen Fayose Hails Nigerian Women On International Women’s Day Earlier, Hon Luka Iliya Zhekaba, the Chairman of the joint committee while presenting the committee’s report thanked the speaker and other Honourable members for given them the assignment and assured of continued commitment to deliver on any assignment given.